Dialogue: 10,0:00:30.31,0:00:35.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,July 3rd, 1957.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:35.36,0:00:38.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto Shinichi, who flew into Osaka \Nfrom Haneda, turned himself in
Dialogue: 10,0:00:38.66,0:00:40.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,at the Osaka Prefectural Police Headquarters
Dialogue: 10,0:00:40.93,0:00:43.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,near the Osaka Castle in the evening. {https://maps.app.goo.gl/jF6sqx1K8WNEAkDL7}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:44.59,0:00:50.24,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,He was immediately investigated \Nfor violating the Public Offices Election Law
Dialogue: 10,0:00:50.24,0:00:53.87,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,and was arrested shortly after 7 p.m., \Njust as he had expected.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:55.25,0:01:01.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Coincidentally, it was exactly the same day \Nand time of day that Toda Josei
Dialogue: 10,0:01:01.02,0:01:04.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was released from prison \N12 years earlier, in July 1945.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:04.50,0:01:10.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Later, Shinichi captured his deepest feelings \Nabout that July 3rd in a haiku.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:22.89,0:01:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Attorney Ozawa just informed us—\NChief Yamamoto has been arrested!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:28.42,0:01:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell? Didn't he turn himself in as a witness? {/person of interest}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:31.77,0:01:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit! Not just Chairman Konishi—\Nnow the Chief as well!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:34.99,0:01:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? What did the Chief do? \NHe hasn't done anything wrong in his life!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:41.04,0:01:42.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Kansai members assumed
Dialogue: 10,0:01:42.75,0:01:47.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the matter was already resolved, \Nsince those directly involved in the bribery
Dialogue: 10,0:01:47.07,0:01:50.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and door-to-door canvassing \Nhad been arrested.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:50.11,0:01:56.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That's why this new development \Nhas caused great shock and outrage.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:02.83,0:02:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oya-san, is he really here?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:05.33,0:02:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They told us last night they moved him \Nto East Police Station.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.83,0:02:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a confirmed info. \NNo doubt about it.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:11.94,0:02:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:14.07,0:02:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:17.20,0:02:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:21.25,0:02:24.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,It'll be fine. \NDon't worry.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:24.58,0:02:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:35.36,0:02:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:38.59,0:02:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto, weren’t those your instructions? \N"Nothing wrong with election fraud."
Dialogue: 10,0:02:45.50,0:02:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Why don't you fucking admit it already?!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:48.54,0:02:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,As I have said many times, \NI have not given such instructions!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:51.82,0:02:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You're one headstrong blabber, aintcha?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.67,0:02:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Even with all the evidence laid out, he keeps insisting he had nothing to do with the bribery.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:59.58,0:03:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of evidence do you have for that? \NWhy don't you show it to me?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:04.71,0:03:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, whatever. \NWe can take it slow, you know.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:08.02,0:03:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway, did you instruct the door-to-door canvassing?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:11.38,0:03:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,At the April 21st briefing at the Kansai headquarters in Tsuruhashi, you said,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:15.36,0:03:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“Please go door-to-door to solicit votes—\NI’ll take full responsibility.”
Dialogue: 10,0:03:20.12,0:03:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't that what happened?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.03,0:03:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No. What I said was, \N"Election fraud would not be tolerated."
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.67,0:03:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit playing dumb with us! \NWe have a witness who testified otherwise!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:31.09,0:03:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then please arrange a meeting between us. \NThere, you'll see at once who's telling the truth.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:35.76,0:03:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. So you want to do it the hard way... {lit: if that's your attitude}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.49,0:03:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Your call! We’ll just have to keep you here
Dialogue: 10,0:03:40.91,0:03:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,for who-knows-how-many more days \Nuntil you come clean!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:43.49,0:03:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's no helping it.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:44.91,0:03:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot possibly admit to what I've never said.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:48.50,0:03:51.61,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On July 8th, Yamamoto's custody
Dialogue: 10,0:03:51.61,0:03:55.47,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,was transferred from East Police Station \Nto Osaka Detention House.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.06,0:04:01.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,Because they’ve locked him up here, \Nthey won’t even allow visits or care packages... {ohiru is "lunch/daytime" so idk what she means, probably means "sending him food"}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:06.75,0:04:13.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,Everyone is just as worried about the Chief as I am and can't sit still...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.55,0:04:20.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,Can't see anything from here... {unsure what she means; 何も見えへん・・・}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:21.30,0:04:26.28,Thought,,0,0,0,,What makes this sorrow so jarring \Nis the fact that we lost this battle. {こないな悲しい思いをするのもうちらが負けたからや}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.28,0:04:30.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,But we definitely can't lose this war!\NWe must win at all costs!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:30.58,0:04:35.08,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,After his transfer to the detention center, \NShinichi’s interrogation
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.08,0:04:38.95,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,was taken over by the Osaka District \NPublic Prosecutors Office.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:38.95,0:04:42.55,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On the very first day, two prosecutors
Dialogue: 10,0:04:42.55,0:04:47.27,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,conducted a grueling interrogation until 11 p.m., denying him dinner.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.75,0:04:52.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But despite all the accusations thrown at him, \NShinichi gave no testimony—
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.34,0:04:55.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,other than to insist \Nhe had done nothing illegal. {affidavit; deposition; testimony}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.67,0:04:59.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The prosecution failed to present any new concrete evidence
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.48,0:05:04.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,that could be considered damning, \Nand time passed in vain.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:04.72,0:05:08.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The prosecution was beginning \Nto feel the weight of responsibility
Dialogue: 10,0:05:08.02,0:05:12.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,for arresting and detaining Yamamoto without being able to extract a confession. {"testimony" last time}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.34,0:05:15.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Then, next afternoon...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:15.59,0:05:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto, because you keep denying everything, we can't progress the investigation.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:21.30,0:05:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,How about we hear what you have to say \Nin the annex interrogation room this time? {annex as in "building annex"}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:26.06,0:05:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.04,0:05:33.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The district prosecutors office and annex were nearby,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:33.27,0:05:38.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but getting there required going outside and being escorted along a public road.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.03,0:05:42.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Out there, you immediately start drawing curious glances from passersby. {/strange}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:42.98,0:05:45.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That kind of humiliating public exposure was intended
Dialogue: 10,0:05:45.94,0:05:48.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to amount to psychological torment for Shinichi. {pilloried criminal exposed to public view; public scorn or humiliation}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:48.92,0:05:54.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, Shinichi stoically endured the humiliation.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:54.08,0:05:58.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A lion remains a lion wherever he goes.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:58.05,0:05:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Ch-Chief...!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:02.38,0:06:06.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Chief hasn't given in to this terrible treatment.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:06.41,0:06:08.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,That means I can't lose either!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:11.25,0:06:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The Chief is handcuffed...\NHow could they?!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:18.64,0:06:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.38,0:06:23.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,How can you lose heart \Nover something like this?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:27.31,0:06:29.37,Top,,0,0,0,,He must be uncuffed immediately! {specifically talks about handcuffs, not just "freed"}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:29.37,0:06:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Ozawa-kun, \Nget them to let Shinichi go at once!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:33.52,0:06:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell the prosecutors—if they were bribed to take down Soka Gakkai, then let them come for me!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.34,0:06:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no way I could stand by \Nand watch my beloved disciple
Dialogue: 10,0:06:42.29,0:06:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,be handcuffed and thrown in jail!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:45.36,0:06:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not gonna run away or hide!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.81,0:06:53.81,Top,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto-kun, why won't you quit playing games and confess?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:54.21,0:06:57.90,Top,,0,0,0,,Everyone arrested for bribery and door-to-door canvassing
Dialogue: 10,0:06:57.90,0:07:00.52,Top,,0,0,0,,claimed they acted on your instructions.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.52,0:07:03.41,Top,,0,0,0,,If so, please let me meet them in person.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:03.90,0:07:06.64,Top,,0,0,0,,After that, there’ll be no doubt it isn’t true.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.64,0:07:08.87,Top,,0,0,0,,Didn't I suggest it many times over?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.26,0:07:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet you refuse to do that. \NWhy won’t you even try to determine the truth?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:16.73,0:07:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All you ever do is pressure me \Nto testify to a blatant lie.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:21.19,0:07:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't admit to what I've never done!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.39,0:07:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re not asking you to lie—
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.99,0:07:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,just suggesting that you'd be better off admitting what needs to be admitted sooner.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.94,0:07:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.45,0:07:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Just think about what could happen \Nif you keep sticking to your guns.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:39.29,0:07:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll have to take action
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.99,0:07:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,against Daito Trading, where you work, and the Soka Gakkai headquarters—
Dialogue: 10,0:07:45.24,0:07:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and when that happens, Toda will go down with them.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:48.28,0:07:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:49.89,0:07:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What does Daito Trading \Nhave to do with this incident?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:53.85,0:07:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It most certainly has no connection \Nto Soka Gakkai {headquarters }or Toda-sensei!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:57.00,0:08:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, it was Toda who appointed you \Nto oversee the elections in Osaka.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.53,0:08:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And Toda is the president \Nof Soka Gakkai himself.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:07.61,0:08:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This incident was organized \Nthrough Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:10.97,0:08:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it natural that we should investigate its president, Toda?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.06,0:08:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:17.50,0:08:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the record, we have confessions stating that Toda approved the bribery.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:24.19,0:08:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a lie!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:25.84,0:08:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's definitely impossible!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.49,0:08:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh well, I guess we'll have \Nto ask Toda personally to find out.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:34.60,0:08:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's me.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:36.29,0:08:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,First things first—\Nget ready to move on Daito Trading.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:40.10,0:08:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And tell the president of Daito Trading \Nto turn over all their books—utmost urgency.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:48.85,0:08:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:50.05,0:08:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.30,0:08:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,With just one word from me, \Nit'll be done in a jiffy.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.49,0:08:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look down on me, \Nyou’ll regret it—big time.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.98,0:09:02.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That afternoon, with two prosecutors watching them closely,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.89,0:09:05.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,attorney Ozawa and Shinichi met
Dialogue: 10,0:09:05.23,0:09:08.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,in the interrogation room \Nof the Osaka Detention House.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:08.90,0:09:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto-kun, please listen carefully \Nto what I'm going to say.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:12.82,0:09:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The prosecutors office has something \Nreally big on its mind this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:18.89,0:09:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{They said that }If you don’t admit to the charges, they’ll raid Daito Trading and the Soka Gakkai headquarters—
Dialogue: 10,0:09:23.74,0:09:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and arrest President Toda.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:26.09,0:09:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The prosecutor said the same to me.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:30.04,0:09:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Looks like they’re really going all out. {/serious about it}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:32.93,0:09:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That brings me to this—
Dialogue: 10,0:09:34.80,0:09:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,why won’t you agree with what the prosecutor says just this once?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:39.44,0:09:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's really worrisome—\Nhearing it from my lawyer of all people!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.28,0:09:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto-kun, the prosecutor \Nis a power to be reckoned with.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.73,0:09:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They can do just about anything if they so desire.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.82,0:09:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And if President Toda were arrested, \Nit would be a major blow to the organization.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.18,0:10:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The prosecutor also said that depending on your behavior, they may settle this quietly. {without fuss; simply - probably means "sweep it under the rug and not make it a public scandalous trial"}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:03.77,0:10:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto-kun, can you \Ncompromise just this once?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.76,0:10:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to satisfy the prosecutor and change your stance starting tomorrow. Please. {lit: testify starting tomorrow - unsure what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:32.40,0:10:40.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,If I admit to that lie by pleading guilty, \Nwhat'll become of the justice we fought for? {lit: what about soka gakkai's justice - think he means "isn't justice the main tenet of soka gakkai?"}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:40.02,0:10:45.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,If I don't, they'll raid the Soka Gakkai headquarters and arrest Toda-sensei...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:50.02,0:10:52.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,If they raid the headquarters...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:55.34,0:10:59.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,The humiliation and terror \Nof our members will be immeasurable.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:59.03,0:11:03.96,Thought,,0,0,0,,And above all, Toda-sensei will be in a world of trouble.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:07.56,0:11:12.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,Still, to let the prosecutor break me \Nby agreeing to a lie?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:13.80,0:11:18.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,Wouldn’t that mean tarnishing my beloved Soka Gakkai with my own hands forever?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:20.35,0:11:22.20,Thought,,0,0,0,,What should I do?!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:26.93,0:11:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do?!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:53.76,0:11:57.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,All I want is for Sensei \Nto stay healthy and live a long life.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:58.57,0:12:01.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,His health is already ailing right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:01.61,0:12:04.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,If he gets arrested now, \NSensei's health would fail.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:05.67,0:12:08.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,That would definitely shorten his lifespan.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:09.27,0:12:11.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,He might even die in prison!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:11.13,0:12:13.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,Why must he go through that?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.92,0:12:20.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,Toda-sensei must absolutely not follow in Makiguchi’s footsteps and die in prison too!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:20.10,0:12:26.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At this point, Shinichi decided \Nto admit his guilt for now
Dialogue: 10,0:12:26.66,0:12:32.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and gamble everything on the trial \Nto prove his innocence in court.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:32.56,0:12:35.38,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On the evening of July 12th,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:35.38,0:12:40.58,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,the Soka Gakkai Tokyo Convention was held at the Kokugikan in Kuramae. {https://maps.app.goo.gl/YPkrLRbYYBGDxC3Y9}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.08,0:12:44.47,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,The 40,000 people gathered in and around the venue
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.47,0:12:48.82,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,erupted in outrage over the unlawful arrest \Nof Chairman Konishi and PR Head Yamamoto
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.82,0:12:55.55,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,by the Osaka District Public Prosecutors Office, \Nraising their voices in fierce protest.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.55,0:12:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We strongly condemn the prosecutors’ unlawful actions
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.52,0:13:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and demand, loud and clear, the immediate release of both Konishi and Yamamoto!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:03.47,0:13:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:05.97,0:13:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe it would be wiser to devote this entire rally to the Q&A session. {rather than a guidance session}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.08,0:13:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead and ask, please. {lit: please, without reservation}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:12.75,0:13:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We all know Chairman Konishi \Nand Chief Yamamoto are in prison right now...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.15,0:13:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you intend to use Soka Gakkai \Nto fight for the release of those two?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:23.20,0:13:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We've found ourselves up against \Nan extremely powerful opponent this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:27.58,0:13:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it's a struggle \Nagainst a powerful enemy,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:30.39,0:13:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,who wields enormous authority.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.21,0:13:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.71,0:13:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,From the day I took office as president, \NI was prepared to lay down my life.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:38.59,0:13:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not scared of anything!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.67,0:13:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Be it the police or the prosecutors, \Nwe'll stand fast in the fight!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.16,0:13:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I ever accept defeat?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:49.20,0:13:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right!\NWe're with you!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:51.22,0:13:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,On the 17th, I will be going to Osaka \Nto give a lecture on the Scriptures.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.24,0:14:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I plan to hold another convention that day \Nand ignite an even greater wave of enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.70,0:14:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that still doesn't work, our next move will be to rally our comrades from across the country.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:07.01,0:14:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I will also put my life on the line.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:09.66,0:14:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us all stand up and fight together!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.34,0:14:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:19.30,0:14:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozawa-san, it seems there'll be a rally \Nat the Public Hall on July 17th.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:24.57,0:14:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re close to reaching an agreement with Yamamoto on his confession,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.19,0:14:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,so let’s have him released by then. {probably means "by 17th"; no clue what the line means in general: 山本の供述も　間もなく一段落しますからそれまでには釈放しましょう = yamamoto's testimony will soon be reaching a stopping place; settling down (before the next stage); getting to a point where one can rest; completing the first stage (of the work) - probably means "pressure yamamoto a bit more to confess and then he'll be free by the time of the convention"}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:30.33,0:14:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:31.45,0:14:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I think for Konishi, we'll even be able \Nto do it a day or two sooner.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:35.06,0:14:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That is much appreciated. Please do.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:49.69,0:14:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They said they'd do it at noon… \Nbut it's getting late!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:53.34,0:14:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think something \Nhas happened to him?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:55.77,0:14:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only been ten minutes, \Nit's not really {\i1}that{\i0} late.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:59.11,0:15:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, it’s been scorching—\Nand they’ve kept him in there for 15 days!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:02.53,0:15:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely, it's been long enough. \NThey ought to free him now or...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:15.31,0:15:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:17.07,0:15:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back, Chief!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.50,0:15:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief Yamamoto!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.87,0:15:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. \NI'm sorry for making you all worry.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.57,0:15:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, I'm well!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.91,0:15:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:33.41,0:15:38.96,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,After that, Shinichi went straight to Itami Airport \Nto meet Toda upon his arrival.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:38.96,0:15:41.36,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,The two of them were to attend
Dialogue: 10,0:15:41.36,0:15:45.59,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,the Osaka Branch Convention \Nat Nakanoshima Public Hall in the evening.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.59,0:15:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m proud to declare the Soka Gakkai Osaka Branch Convention officially open!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:50.93,0:15:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.58,0:16:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on? \NHeavens wrath? {various deities; the gods}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.02,0:16:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:05.26,0:16:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's raining!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.80,0:16:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,My dear friends, both here \Nand outside the venue—it's been a while!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:22.84,0:16:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize for causing you \Nthis much worry for such a long time.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:26.84,0:16:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,At noon today, I was released from prison \Nwith my spirit unbowed—
Dialogue: 10,0:16:31.09,0:16:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I owe it to the protection of the Lotus Sutra! {/full of energy - idk, doesn't sound very post-jailtime-like}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:34.58,0:16:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your support!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:39.98,0:16:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,On account of my imprisonment, Toda-sensei said, "One of the three formidable enemies—
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.90,0:16:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the overbearing false saints \Nmade an appearance!" {僭聖増上慢 = boastfully usurping saint wrongly believing to have attained enlightenment​}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:48.49,0:16:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Firmly believing in Nichiren Daishonin's golden maxim,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:51.70,0:16:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"Great evil portends \Nthe arrival of great good,"
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.20,0:16:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I am determined to strengthen my faith
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.83,0:17:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and work hard alongside all of you \Nfor the achievement of the Common Path!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:05.48,0:17:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us move forward with the conviction
Dialogue: 10,0:17:08.48,0:17:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that unwavering faith and true Buddhism \Nwill ultimately prevail!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:13.35,0:17:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:14.81,0:17:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:18.65,0:17:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s make this a two-way conversation \Nand move on to the Q&A session.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:23.85,0:17:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:24.38,0:17:25.23,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.61,0:17:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:27.80,0:17:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The newspapers have been publishing \Nnothing but fabrications
Dialogue: 10,0:17:31.69,0:17:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,about Soka Gakkai \Nconcerning the recent incident. {lit: facts that are completely different from reality}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:34.64,0:17:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do to correct them?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:37.04,0:17:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,As you've just said, everything they publish \Nis hogwash that has nothing to do with the truth.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:42.85,0:17:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what the media say, \Nit's not even worth consideration. {of no concern at all; I couldn't care less; no skin off my nose}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.03,0:17:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.96,0:17:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This whole business \Nmade quite the name for us.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:50.65,0:17:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we shouldn't be angry \Nat free promotion.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:53.93,0:17:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:55.47,0:17:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think the journalists believe in? {だいたい彼らに　いかなる信念がありますか}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:58.90,0:18:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If a war were to break out, they’d be \Nthe first to cheer it on from the front row.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:04.04,0:18:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And once peace is restored, they suddenly become pacifists with a spotless conscience.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:09.11,0:18:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, any discussion without integrity is like smoke. {/without faith - think he means by extension "Devotion to your convictions"}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:12.82,0:18:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you just keep quiet about what they write, \Nthe world will automatically assume it's true.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:19.10,0:18:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to say exactly what I need to say.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.12,0:18:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:23.58,0:18:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Once again, while they rely on hearsay and speculation,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:27.12,0:18:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we speak with firsthand knowledge of the truth about Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:31.49,0:18:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt that our position is stronger.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:34.50,0:18:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A war of words takes many forms beyond print.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.84,0:18:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, what’s more powerful than a face-to-face conversation? {lit: isn't the ultimate discussion the one that's in real speech/natural voice (without a microphone)}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:42.52,0:18:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How can justice be defeated by a bunch of lies?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:46.79,0:18:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Justice will prevail—but its victory should never be taken for granted. {lit: "justice will win" but that is not the supreme truth}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.56,0:18:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If we stop fighting, \Njustice will be trampled.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:54.38,0:18:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as Soka Gakkai is just, it cannot lose. {lit: when it comes to justice, gakkai can't lose}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:58.35,0:19:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddhism is a battle \Nthat we absolutely need to win!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:02.18,0:19:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we keep fighting!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:04.12,0:19:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.37,0:19:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This concludes the Q&A session.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.58,0:19:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t need to worry \Nabout what comes next—
Dialogue: 10,0:19:10.40,0:19:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as you keep chanting \Nand stay strong in spirit, happiness {\i1}will{\i0} follow.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:15.61,0:19:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That is my primary desire!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:28.42,0:19:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:29.74,0:19:30.46,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Chief!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:30.77,0:19:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:40.07,0:19:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let's sing!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:02.91,0:20:09.85,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,My comrades in Kansai who grieved, \Ngrew angry, and prayed for me—thank you all.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.86,0:20:14.58,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,I will fight with my life for the friendships I've made in Kansai for as long as I live!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:16.51,0:20:19.82,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,At the end of July, \NYamamoto Shinichi was indicted
Dialogue: 10,0:20:19.82,0:20:24.60,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,by the Osaka District Public Prosecutors' Office
Dialogue: 10,0:20:24.60,0:20:28.84,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,as the alleged organizer \Nof the door-to-door canvassing campaign.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:28.84,0:20:33.00,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,But after four and a half years \Nof intense legal battles,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.00,0:20:38.97,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,at the final and 84th hearing in January 1962\Nhe was acquitted of all charges.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:38.97,0:20:42.93,Top,,0,0,0,,Defendant Yamamoto Shinichi—found innocent!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:42.93,0:20:48.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Thus, Shinichi’s innocence was upheld, \Ntruth triumphed over deception and intrigue,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:48.86,0:20:52.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and the justness of Soka Gakkai \Nwas made clear to the world. {literal, could go for "righteousness"}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:52.40,0:20:57.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was also a victory \Nin the struggle for human rights—
Dialogue: 10,0:20:57.30,0:21:00.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,affirming dignity, freedom, and equality,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:00.30,0:21:05.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and exonerating those falsely accused and oppressed by state power.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:08.08,0:21:12.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,Today, East and West—most notably the United States and the Soviet Union—
Dialogue: 10,0:21:12.37,0:21:15.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,are locked in a race to develop \Never more powerful nuclear weapons,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:15.69,0:21:18.93,Thought,,0,0,0,,testing atomic and hydrogen bombs \Nwithout restraint.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:19.59,0:21:24.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,If we leave things as they are, \Nthe annihilation of Earth and humanity
Dialogue: 10,0:21:24.45,0:21:27.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,by atomic and hydrogen bombs \Nwill become inevitable.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.55,0:21:30.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,As Buddhists, our mission
Dialogue: 10,0:21:30.31,0:21:35.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,is to enforce the abolition \Nof atomic and hydrogen bombs at all costs.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:35.54,0:21:42.26,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,What's matters is not capitalism or communism—\Nlet's not let ourselves be swayed by their ideology.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:42.26,0:21:46.43,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,We must reach a shared understanding that atomic and hydrogen bombs
Dialogue: 10,0:21:46.43,0:21:51.69,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,are an “absolute evil” threatening humanity’s very right to survive.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:52.65,0:21:56.30,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, we must reaffirm that those who use atomic and hydrogen bombs—
Dialogue: 10,0:21:56.30,0:21:58.46,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,the demonic creations of human hands—
Dialogue: 10,0:21:58.46,0:22:01.22,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,are themselves no better than devils. {lit: use/utilize/employ - not sure what he means, obviously individuals can't use it, so maybe he means the country leaders, maybe he means "those who maintain/produce"}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:01.65,0:22:04.98,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,In the name of everything humane, \Nwe must never come to terms with it. {/humanity}{/let it pass}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:05.63,0:22:06.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,Never!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:07.66,0:22:12.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,It is our duty to instill this conviction \Nin the hearts of people around the world.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:18.95,0:22:22.23,Thought,,0,0,0,,I've been feeling rather unwell lately.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:22.68,0:22:25.87,Thought,,0,0,0,,Something has changed from before...
Dialogue: 10,0:22:25.87,0:22:29.27,Thought,,0,0,0,,My energy feels just as strong as ever,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:29.27,0:22:33.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,but I can’t shake the sense that some kind of blockage is building deep within me. {stagnation; tie-up; standstill; congestion; delay; accumulation}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:36.44,0:22:43.97,Thought,,0,0,0,,Perhaps this is because life itself senses \Nthat it has little time left to live.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:44.49,0:22:48.93,Thought,,0,0,0,,In that case, I must perfect everything \NI’m meant to do in this life.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:51.66,0:22:56.85,Thought,,0,0,0,,This declaration I will make tomorrow at the Youth Festival to abolish all nuclear weapons
Dialogue: 10,0:22:56.85,0:23:01.74,Thought,,0,0,0,,will stand as my ultimate message \Nto future generations and my foremost legacy. {lit: anti-atomic and hydrogen bomb declaration will become the first instruction to the youth and what I leave behind - sounds like he plans to leave behind several types of legacy and this one is the first or something; or he just means "the most important"}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:04.88,0:23:09.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On September 8th, under clear skies after the typhoon,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:09.16,0:23:13.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the Youth Division East Japan Athletic Meet and the Youth Festival
Dialogue: 10,0:23:13.12,0:23:17.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was held at the Yokohama Mitsuzawa Stadium.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:21.26,0:23:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:38.31,0:23:43.76,Thought,,0,0,0,,This midsummer sun was shining just as brightly
Dialogue: 10,0:23:43.76,0:23:49.79,Thought,,0,0,0,,on August 6, 1945, when the world's first atomic bomb was dropped on Hiroshima...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:50.43,0:23:54.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,We must break free once and for all \Nfrom this demonic claw
Dialogue: 10,0:23:54.41,0:23:56.79,Thought,,0,0,0,,that robs us of our very right to survive!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:03.21,0:24:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to announce to you all \Nmy first lasting message for future generations. {teachings left by a deceased person; last instructions}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:09.59,0:24:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I will make my position unmistakably clear
Dialogue: 10,0:24:13.10,0:24:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,on the nuclear and hydrogen bomb tests \Nthat are shaking society today.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:22.40,0:24:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A movement calling for a ban \Non the testing of nuclear weapons {largely from https://www.joseitoda.org/vision/declaration/ from here on}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:26.53,0:24:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,has arisen around the world.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:28.91,0:24:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But I want to expose and rip out \Nthe devil's claws that lie hidden
Dialogue: 10,0:24:33.35,0:24:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in the very depths of such weapons. {called atomic}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:36.86,0:24:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we, the citizens of the world, \Nhave an inviolable right to live.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:42.69,0:24:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone who jeopardizes that right \Nis a devil incarnate, a Satan, a monster.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:49.45,0:24:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if one country, no matter which one, \Nwins with an atomic bomb,
Dialogue: 10,0:24:56.50,0:25:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I maintain that anyone who ventures \Nto use these weapons,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:01.17,0:25:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,should be sentenced to death without exception.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:03.84,0:25:05.20,Thought,,0,0,0,,To death?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:07.06,0:25:10.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,I see—Sensei seeks to condemn to death
Dialogue: 10,0:25:10.64,0:25:16.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,the very evil lurking within life \Nthat drives a wedge into the human heart
Dialogue: 10,0:25:16.12,0:25:21.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,and makes justifying the use of nuclear weapons possible!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:21.18,0:25:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if a country should conquer the world \Nthrough the use of nuclear weapons,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:28.53,0:25:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the conquerors must be viewed as devils, as evil incarnate.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:33.41,0:25:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe that it is the mission of every member
Dialogue: 10,0:25:35.93,0:25:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,of the youth division in Japan \Nto disseminate this idea throughout the globe.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:41.50,0:25:44.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This historic "Declaration for the Abolition of Nuclear Weapons,"
Dialogue: 10,0:25:44.71,0:25:47.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,which sparked the global \NSoka Gakkai peace movement,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:48.05,0:25:52.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,would become Toda’s foremost message \Nto the Youth Division. {/legacy/last instructions}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:53.32,0:25:57.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,We must ensure without fail \Nthat Sensei’s instruction is fulfilled. {/lasting message}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:57.66,0:26:06.28,Thought,,0,0,0,,I will make it my lifelong mission to spread Sensei's teachings throughout the world!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:09.39,0:26:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Yamamoto.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:10.65,0:26:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Shinichi? Come in.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:16.14,0:26:20.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei has been lying \Non the sofa a lot these days ...
Dialogue: 10,0:26:21.04,0:26:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher, how are you feeling?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:24.46,0:26:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine. \NJust a little tired, that's all.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:29.13,0:26:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as he still has a lot to do,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:33.43,0:26:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,a man can't die that easily.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:37.96,0:26:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:39.77,0:26:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, sit down.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:45.98,0:26:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I have sacrificed my own life \Nto the noble cause of the Common Path.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:52.86,0:27:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Living for a noble and supreme goal can instill anyone with great strength and determination.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:02.23,0:27:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When I became the president, \NI vowed to convert 750,000 households.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:08.86,0:27:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as I live,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:11.36,0:27:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I will devote myself to personally spreading the Lotus Sutra to 750,000 households!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:19.03,0:27:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like we’re finally about to make it, even though no one took me seriously at the start.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:25.00,0:27:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, it didn't play out \Nthe way I envisioned it. {lit: I was taking no notice (of); thinking nothing of; disregarding; not aware of; completely ignoring; being out of consideration about that kind of thing - no idea what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:30.13,0:27:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I wanted to do it on my own.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:33.49,0:27:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have to rely on others, \Nyou can't fight a real battle. {lit: if you have the heart to ask someone for help}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:38.10,0:27:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,When you rely on others, \Nyou seek strength in numbers—
Dialogue: 10,0:27:40.79,0:27:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that means you've already been defeated in your heart. {think that's what he means}{/that kind of mindset is the root of defeat}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:45.94,0:27:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I've dedicated my life to paving a broad road \Ninto the future for the Common Path.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:53.40,0:27:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But it falls to you guys to give \Nyour grand performance on that stage. {/to act}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:59.30,0:28:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:01.18,0:28:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it falls to you!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:02.85,0:28:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:03.95,0:28:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let me down, Shinichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:05.93,0:28:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:07.46,0:28:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the battle for the Common Path begins, \Nwe must win it at all costs.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:13.73,0:28:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing brings greater shame to a person \Nthan losing a battle he started!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:19.42,0:28:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:21.37,0:28:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,do you understand?
Dialogue: 10,0:28:23.08,0:28:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:28.39,0:28:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,A word from president: Toda Josei-sensei!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:34.82,0:28:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What I’d like to ask is this:
Dialogue: 10,0:28:38.28,0:28:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“What do you believe is the driving force \Nbehind Soka Gakkai’s growth?”
Dialogue: 10,0:28:42.78,0:28:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, it's clear:
Dialogue: 10,0:28:45.18,0:28:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai has faith. \NIt has the Lotus Sutra.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:48.79,0:28:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This merit of piety is where it all originates!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:52.63,0:28:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:53.96,0:28:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at things honestly, \Nit'll become immediately obvious.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:57.92,0:29:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But for some reason, scholars, critics, \Nand journalists refuse to realize this. {/commentators}
Dialogue: 10,0:29:04.28,0:29:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai is formed around faith. \NFaith is our lifeblood.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:08.87,0:29:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Our purpose is neither to engage in politics
Dialogue: 10,0:29:11.62,0:29:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,nor to interfere in the economy—\Nwe were not established for such ends.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:16.55,0:29:20.58,Top,,0,0,0,,We support our comrades entering politics \Nto better society
Dialogue: 10,0:29:20.58,0:29:24.03,Top,,0,0,0,,and implement policies \Nthat truly serve the people—
Dialogue: 10,0:29:24.03,0:29:27.63,Top,,0,0,0,,that is the genuine expression of our intent. {/make the people happy}
Dialogue: 10,0:29:28.23,0:29:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The ultimate intention of Soka Gakkai
Dialogue: 10,0:29:32.18,0:29:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is to bring happiness to the people of Japan \Nand the world through the power of faith.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:38.26,0:29:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:39.80,0:29:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as you hold fast to this conviction,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:43.22,0:29:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,no amount of blatant and outrageous criticism \Nin the media will be able to discompose you.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:49.02,0:29:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If just seeing your faith mentioned in a magazine \Nleaves you shaken and stammering,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:53.58,0:29:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,then this faith isn't for you! {/quit believing}
Dialogue: 10,0:29:56.46,0:29:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This concludes my address.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:58.99,0:29:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:30:00.49,0:30:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:30:01.36,0:30:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing worth printing here! {/This is no way to write an article.}
Dialogue: 10,0:30:03.32,0:30:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:30:06.28,0:30:08.14,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei's footing is unsteady.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:10.98,0:30:12.79,Thought,,0,0,0,,So he really is unwell...
Dialogue: 10,0:30:12.79,0:30:16.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda was already ailing by then.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:16.87,0:30:22.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But in his heart, the flame of determination to push through every obstacle
Dialogue: 10,0:30:22.76,0:30:28.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and take another step forward \Nstill burned brightly.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:29.12,0:30:34.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That same fire also raged in Shinichi's heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:34.18,0:30:38.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,No matter what happens, I’ll always be there \Nto lend Toda-sensei my shoulder
Dialogue: 10,0:30:38.46,0:30:42.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,and move forward on the Common Path \Ntowards eternity alongside my mentor.
